Description: Fragment of deeply concave lip of Attic black-glazed pottery open vase, probably type C cup. Wholly glazed. Incised inscription on outside.
Bibliographic references: Edgar 1898/1899 / Excavations at Naukratis. B: The Inscribed and Painted Pottery (no. 79)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 702, no. 602)
Höckmann & Möller 2006 / The Hellenion at Naukratis: Questions and Observations (p.14, fig.7, 13)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1703)
